          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="TipOfTheDayBulb.jpg" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:328px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">You can move a method to a particular category by holding down the SHIFT key and dragging the method over the category in the class or system browser. </text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">When you move a method to a category in this way it is removed from all other categories apart from pseudo-categories such as public/private. If you want to retain the existing categories then just use a plain drag copy operation (without the SHIFT).</text><snippet src="Tip_Of_The_Day_Footer"/></para>
